subSubSection.paragraph:
Male (
Fig. 3a, b
): Inner laterotergites not distinct. Distal margin of tergite VII straight. Posterior margins of sternites III–IV straight, V slightly, VI strongly concaved cephalad. Mid length of sternite VI about one third of sternite VII. Pygophore: median projection with median longitudinal ridge; anterolateral margin of median projection with horn-like outgrowth (
Figs. 1e
; 
3e
). Paramere and phallotheca shown in 
Figs. 1
f–i; 3f–j.

Female (
Fig. 3c, d
): Inner laterotergites III–VI present. Anterior margin of tergite VIII with anterolateral apodemes (as 
Fig. 9k
). Median line of sternites I–V weakly sclerotized. Middle margins of the two halves of sternite VII curved and slightly overlapping (
Fig. 4f
), but looks separate when dissected (
Fig. 3d
). Ovipositor with first and second gonapophysis narrow and elongate. Spermatheca weakly sclerotized; bulb gourd-like, without any rim or flange; duct short, about three times length of bulb.
